1253  if (MMWave_start(gMmwMCB.ctrlHandle, &calibrationCfg, &errCode) < 0)
1254  {
1255  MMWave_ErrorLevel errorLevel;
1256  int16_t mmWaveErrorCode;
1257  int16_t subsysErrorCode;
1258 
1259  /* Error/Warning: Unable to start the mmWave module */
1260  MMWave_decodeError (errCode, &errorLevel, &mmWaveErrorCode, &subsysErrorCode);
1261  System_printf ("Error: mmWave Start failed [mmWave Error: %d Subsys: %d]\n", mmWaveErrorCode, subsysErrorCode);
1262  /* datapath has already been moved to start state; so either we initiate a cleanup of start sequence or
1263  assert here and re-start from the beginning. For now, choosing the latter path */
1264  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1265  return -1;
1266  }
1267 
1268  /*****************************************************************************
1269  * The sensor has been started successfully. Switch on the LED
1270  *****************************************************************************/
1271  GPIO_write (gMmwMCB.cfg.platformCfg.SensorStatusGPIO, 1U);
1272 
1273  gMmwMCB.sensorStartCount++;

1290 static uint16_t MmwDemo_convertCfarToLinear(uint16_t codedCfarVal, uint8_t numVirtualAntennas)
1291 {
1292  uint16_t linearVal;
1293  float dbVal, linVal;
1294 
1295  /* dbVal is a float value from 0-100dB. It needs to
1296  be converted to linear scale..
1297  First, recover float dbVal that was encoded in CLI. */
1298  dbVal = (float)(codedCfarVal / MMWDEMO_CFAR_THRESHOLD_ENCODING_FACTOR);
1299 
1300  /* Now convert it to linear value according to the following:
1301  linear_value = dB_value * (256 / 6) * (numVirtualAntennas / (2^ ceil(log2(numVirtualAntennas)))) .
1302  */
1303  linVal = dbVal * (256.0 / 6.0) * ((float)numVirtualAntennas / (float)(1 << mathUtils_ceilLog2(numVirtualAntennas)));
1304 
1305  linearVal = (uint16_t) linVal;
1306  return (linearVal);
1307 }

1317 void MmwDemo_stopSensor()
1318 {
1319  int32_t errCode;
1320 
1321  MmwDemo_MMWave_stop();
1322 
1323  /* Wait until DPM_stop is completed */
1324  Semaphore_pend(gMmwMCB.DPMstopSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
1325 
1326  /* Delete any active streaming session */
1327  if(gMmwMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle != NULL)
1328  {
1329  /* Evaluate need to deactivate h/w session:
1330  * One sub-frame case:
1331  * if h/w only enabled, deactivation never happened, hence need to deactivate
1332  * if h/w and s/w both enabled, then s/w would leave h/w activated when it is done
1333  * so need to deactivate
1334  * (only s/w enabled cannot be the case here because we are checking for non-null h/w session)
1335  * Multi sub-frame case:
1336  * Given stop, we must have re-configured the next sub-frame by now which is next of the
1337  * last sub-frame i.e we must have re-configured sub-frame 0. So if sub-frame 0 had
1338  * h/w enabled, then it is left in active state and need to deactivate. For all
1339  * other cases, h/w was already deactivated when done.
1340  */
1341  if ((gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames == 1) ||
1342  ((gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames > 1) &&
1343  (gMmwMCB.subFrameCfg[0].lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt != MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED))
1344  )
1345  {
1346  if (CBUFF_deactivateSession(gMmwMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
1347  {
1348  System_printf("CBUFF_deactivateSession failed with errorCode = %d\n", errCode);
1349  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1350  }
1351  }
1352  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteHwSession();
1353  }
1354 
1355  /* Delete s/w session if it exists. S/w session never needs to be deactivated in stop because
1356  * it always (unconditionally) deactivates itself upon completion.
1357  */
1358  if(gMmwMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle != NULL)
1359  {
1360  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteSwSession();
1361  }
1362 
1363  MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog();
1364 
1365  /* The sensor has been stopped successfully. Switch off the LED */
1366  GPIO_write (gMmwMCB.cfg.platformCfg.SensorStatusGPIO, 0U);
1367 
1368  gMmwMCB.sensorStopCount++;
1369 
1370  /* print for user */
1371  System_printf("Sensor has been stopped: startCount: %d stopCount %d\n",
1372  gMmwMCB.sensorStartCount,gMmwMCB.sensorStopCount);
1373 }

1887  {
1888  /* Received Asychronous Message: */
1889  switch (asyncSB)
1890  {
1891  case RL_RF_AE_CPUFAULT_SB:
1892  {
1893  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1894  break;
1895  }
1896  case RL_RF_AE_ESMFAULT_SB:
1897  {
1898  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1899  break;
1900  }
1901  case RL_RF_AE_ANALOG_FAULT_SB:
1902  {
1903  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1904  break;
1905  }
1906  case RL_RF_AE_INITCALIBSTATUS_SB:
1907  {
1908  rlRfInitComplete_t* ptrRFInitCompleteMessage;
1909  uint32_t calibrationStatus;
1910 
1911  /* Get the RF-Init completion message: */
1912  ptrRFInitCompleteMessage = (rlRfInitComplete_t*)payload;
1913  calibrationStatus = ptrRFInitCompleteMessage->calibStatus & 0xFFFU;
1914 
1915  /* Display the calibration status: */
1916  CLI_write ("Debug: Init Calibration Status = 0x%x\n", calibrationStatus);
1917  break;
1918  }
1919  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_TRIGGER_RDY_SB:
1920  {
1921  gMmwMCB.stats.frameTriggerReady++;
1922  break;
1923  }
1924  case RL_RF_AE_MON_TIMING_FAIL_REPORT_SB:
1925  {
1926  gMmwMCB.stats.failedTimingReports++;
1927  break;
1928  }
1929  case RL_RF_AE_RUN_TIME_CALIB_REPORT_SB:
1930  {
1931  gMmwMCB.stats.calibrationReports++;
1932  break;
1933  }
1934  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_END_SB:
1935  {
1936  gMmwMCB.stats.sensorStopped++;
1937 
1938  DebugP_log0("App: BSS stop (frame end) received\n");
1939 
1940  MmwDemo_dataPathStop(&gMmwMCB.dataPathObj);
1941  break;
1942  }
1943  default:
1944  {
1945  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous Event SB Id %d not handled\n", asyncSB);
1946  break;
1947  }
1948  }
1949  break;
1950  }
1951  /* Async Event from MMWL */
1952  case RL_MMWL_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:
1953  {
1954  switch (asyncSB)
1955  {
1956  case RL_MMWL_AE_MISMATCH_REPORT:
1957  {
1958  /* link reports protocol error in the async report from BSS */
1959  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1960  break;
1961  }
1962  case RL_MMWL_AE_INTERNALERR_REPORT:
1963  {
1964  /* link reports internal error during BSS communication */
1965  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
1966  break;
1967  }
1968  }
1969  break;
1970  }
1971  default:
1972  {
1973  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
1974  break;
1975  }
1976  }
1977  return 0;
1978 }

2742 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
2743 {
2744  int32_t retVal;
2745  DPM_Buffer resultBuffer;
2746  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResultExportedInfo exportInfo;
2747  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result;
2748

2750  {

2753  if (retVal < 0) {
2754  System_printf ("Error: DPM execution failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
2755  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2756  }
2757  else
2758  {
2759  if (resultBuffer.size[0] == sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult))
2760  {
2761  volatile uint32_t startTime, currentInterFrameProcessingEndTime;
2762  MmwDemo_SubFrameStats *currSubFrameStats, *prevSubFrameStats;
2763  uint16_t dummyRxChanOffset[SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL];
2764 
2765  uint8_t numSubFrames;
2766  uint8_t nextSubFrameIndx, prevSubFrameIndx, currSubFrameIndx;
2767 
2768  result = (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *)resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0];
2769  currSubFrameIndx = result->subFrameIdx;
2770  currSubFrameStats = &gMmwMCB.subFrameStats[currSubFrameIndx];
2771 
2772  currentInterFrameProcessingEndTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2773  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingTime =
2774  (currentInterFrameProcessingEndTime - result->stats->interFrameStartTimeStamp)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2775 
2776  numSubFrames = gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames;
2777 
2778  /* Update the processing end margin, note this is of the previous sub-frame
2779  * and should work even when there is only 1 sub-frame (or non-advanced mode)
2780  * as long as end time stamp is updated after using it. Note that
2781  * "result->stats->subFramePreparationCycles" is of the previous sub-frame's
2782  * preparation for the next (which is the current here) because sub-frame
2783  * preparation happens when DPC processes the results exported IOCTL which
2784  * is issued after all the result handling here. However, we also store
2785  * this after using for debug purposes (to be able to see all sub-frames switching cycles
2786  * in real-time)
2787  */
2788  prevSubFrameIndx = MmwDemo_getPrevSubFrameIndx(currSubFrameIndx, numSubFrames);
2789  prevSubFrameStats = &gMmwMCB.subFrameStats[prevSubFrameIndx];
2790  prevSubFrameStats->outputStats.interFrameProcessingMargin =
2791  (result->stats->frameStartTimeStamp - prevSubFrameStats->interFrameProcessingEndTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ -
2792  (result->stats->subFramePreparationCycles/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ + prevSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime) -
2793  prevSubFrameStats->pendingConfigProcTime;
2794 
2795  /* Below is only for debug purposes */
2796  prevSubFrameStats->objDetSubFramePreparationTime = result->stats->subFramePreparationCycles/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2797 
2798  /* This must be after above prevSubFrame processing */
2799  currSubFrameStats->interFrameProcessingEndTime = currentInterFrameProcessingEndTime;
2800 
2801  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2802 
2803  /* Send out of CLI the range bias and phase config measurement if it was enabled. */
2804  if (gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.measureRxChannelBiasCfg.enabled == 1)
2805  {
2806  if (result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement != NULL)
2807  {
2808  MmwDemo_measurementResultOutput(result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement);
2809  }
2810  else
2811  {
2812  /* DPC is not ready to ship the measurement results */
2813  }
2814  }
2815 
2816  if (gMmwMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIndx].lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt !=
2817  MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED)
2818  {
2819  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for the current sub-frame's
2820  * h/w session that is expected to be completed by now */
2821  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors(MMW_LVDS_STREAM_EDMA_INSTANCE);
2822 
2823  /* Pend for completion of h/w session, generally this will not wait
2824  * because of time spent doing inter-frame processing is expected to
2825  * be bigger than the transmission of the h/w session */
2826  Semaphore_pend(gMmwMCB.lvdsStream.hwFrameDoneSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
2827  }
2828 
2829  /* Transfer data on LVDS if s/w session is enabled for the current sub-frame */
2830  if(gMmwMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIndx].lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled == 1)
2831  {
2832  MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData(currSubFrameIndx, result);
2833  }
2834 
2835  MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput(gMmwMCB.loggingUartHandle, result,
2836  &currSubFrameStats->outputStats);
2837 
2838  /* Wait until s/w session is complete. We expect the LVDS transmission of
2839  * s/w session to be completed by now because the UART transmission above is slower.
2840  * Doing the wait immediately after starting the transmission above MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData
2841  * will serialize the LVDS and UART transfers so it is better to do after UART
2842  * transmission (which is blocking call i.e UART transmission is completed when we exit
2843  * out of above MmwDemo_transmitProcessedOutput). Note we cannot replace below code
2844  * with check for previous sub-frame s/w session completion before the
2845  * MmwDemo_transferLVDSUserData above because we need to ensure that
2846  * current sub-frame/frame's contents are not being read during the
2847  * next sub-frame/frame transmission, presently the data that is being
2848  * transmitted is not double buffered to allow this */
2849  if(gMmwMCB.subFrameCfg[currSubFrameIndx].lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled == 1)
2850  {
2851  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for the s/w session
2852  * that is expected to be completed by now */
2853  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors(MMW_LVDS_STREAM_EDMA_INSTANCE);
2854 
2855  /* Pend completion of s/w session, no wait is expected here */
2856  Semaphore_pend(gMmwMCB.lvdsStream.swFrameDoneSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
2857  }
2858 
2859  currSubFrameStats->outputStats.transmitOutputTime =
2860  (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2861 
2862  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2863 
2864  /* For non-advanced frame case:
2865  * process all pending dynamic config commands.
2866  * For advanced-frame case:
2867  * Process next sub-frame related pending dynamic config commands.
2868  * If the next sub-frame was the first sub-frame of the frame,
2869  * then process common (sub-frame independent) pending dynamic config
2870  * commands. */
2871  nextSubFrameIndx = MmwDemo_getNextSubFrameIndx(currSubFrameIndx,
2872  numSubFrames);
2873  retVal = MmwDemo_processPendingDynamicCfgCommands(nextSubFrameIndx);
2874  if (retVal != 0)
2875  {
2876  System_printf ("Error: Executing Pending Dynamic Configuration Commands for nextSubFrameIndx = %d [Error code %d]\n",
2877  nextSubFrameIndx, retVal);
2878  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2879  }
2880 
2881  currSubFrameStats->pendingConfigProcTime =
2882  (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2883 
2884  /* Configure ADC for next sub-frame */
2885  if (numSubFrames > 1)
2886  {
2887  MmwDemo_SubFrameCfg *nextSubFrameCfg;
2888 
2889  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
2890 
2891  nextSubFrameCfg = &gMmwMCB.subFrameCfg[nextSubFrameIndx];
2892  retVal = MmwDemo_ADCBufConfig(gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.adcbufHandle,
2893  gMmwMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg.rxChannelEn,
2894  nextSubFrameCfg->numChirpsPerChirpEvent,
2895  nextSubFrameCfg->adcBufChanDataSize,
2896  &nextSubFrameCfg->adcBufCfg,
2897  &dummyRxChanOffset[0]);
2898  if (retVal < 0)
2899  {
2900  System_printf("Error: ADCBuf config failed with error [%d]\n", retVal);
2901  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
2902  }
2903 
2904  /* Configure HW LVDS stream for this subframe? */
2905  if(nextSubFrameCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt != MMW_DEMO_LVDS_STREAM_CFG_DATAFMT_DISABLED)
2906  {
2907  /* check Edma errors (which are considered fatal) for any previous session, even
2908  * though we have checked for a previous s/w session, if s/w session weren't
2909  * enabled, then this will check for previous h/w session related Edma errors */
2910  MmwDemo_checkEdmaErrors(MMW_LVDS_STREAM_EDMA_INSTANCE);
2911 
2912  MmwDemo_configLVDSHwData(nextSubFrameIndx);
2913  }
2914 
2915  currSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime =
2916  (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/R4F_CLOCK_MHZ;
2917  }
2918  else
2919  {
2920  currSubFrameStats->subFramePreparationTime = 0;
2921  }
2922 
2923  /* indicate result consumed and end of frame/sub-frame processing */
2924  exportInfo.subFrameIdx = currSubFrameIndx;
2925  retVal = DPM_ioctl (gMmwMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle,
2926  DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__DYNAMIC_EXECUTE_RESULT_EXPORTED,
2927  &exportInfo,
2928  sizeof (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResultExportedInfo));
2929  if (retVal < 0) {
2930  System_printf ("Error: DPM DPC_OBJDET_IOCTL__DYNAMIC_EXECUTE_RESULT_EXPORTED failed [Error code %d]\n",
2931  retVal);
2932  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
2933  }
2934  }
2935  }
2936  }
